# el-capitan

Route `crew <command>` triggers to the right crew member. If the message doesn't start with `crew` (or `@crew-researcher`), respond normally — no routing.

## Routing table

| Trigger | Crew member |
|---|---|
| `crew spec` issue/URL/description | crew-specwriter |
| `crew implement` | crew-implement → @crew-builder |
| `crew diff` | crew-diff |
| `crew commit` | crew-commit |
| `crew open pr` | crew-open-pr |
| `crew review` [PR #X \| spec \| (self)] | crew-reviewer |
| `crew address PR` #X or URL | crew-pr-resolver |
| `crew eval`: suggestion | crew-eval-pr-comments |
| `crew log` | crew-log |
| `crew recall`: question | crew-recall |
| `crew brainstorm` or + topic | crew-thinker |
| `crew learn` X or URL | crew-route-learn rule → @crew-researcher or @crew-thinker |
| `crew create issue` description | crew-create-issue |
| `crew cleanup` | crew-cleanup |
| `crew automations` | crew-automations |
| `crew autopilot` | crew-orchestrator (auto-advance to next gate) |
| `crew status` | crew-orchestrator (print pipeline state) |

**This table is authoritative.** Do not override it with judgment calls.

## Subagent dispatch

Some crew members do heavy exploration and should run as isolated subagents (Cursor Task tool) to avoid polluting the orchestrator's context. Others are lightweight and run inline.

| Command | Dispatch | subagent_type |
|---|---|---|
| `crew spec` | **Subagent** | `crew-specwriter` |
| `crew review` | **Subagent** | `crew-reviewer` |
| `crew learn` (researcher path) | **Subagent** | `crew-researcher` |
| `crew brainstorm` | **Subagent** | `crew-thinker` |
| `crew implement` | **Subagent** (via crew-implement skill) | `crew-builder` |
| All other commands | **Inline** | — |

**How to launch a subagent:** Use the Task tool with the `subagent_type` from the table. Pass a detailed prompt containing all context the agent needs (repo, branch, issue URL, user input, recalled patterns). The subagent runs autonomously and returns its result.

**Claude Code fallback:** When the Task tool is unavailable (Claude Code), read the agent file directly and follow its protocol inline. Agents that dispatch sub-subagents (personas) document their own Claude Code fallback — typically spawning parallel `claude` CLI processes or running persona protocols inline sequentially. Agent files live at `~/.claude/agents/<name>.md` with persona subdirectories at `~/.claude/agents/<name>/<role-plural>/`.

## Add-ons

Skills/agents in `~/.cursor/` that are regular files (not symlinks) are add-ons. Route to them by matching the user's trigger to their description frontmatter.

## Invariants

- Explicit routing only — `crew` prefix required
- **`crew implement` always follows crew-builder's protocol.** Code changes go through crew-builder — via ralph, subagent, or inline protocol. Never skip the protocol and implement ad-hoc.
- Pipeline state, task resolution, and gate logic live in `crew-orchestrator.mdc` — the router only dispatches.
